Source: dbmail
Section: mail
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Paul J Stevens <paul@nfg.nl>
Build-Depends: automake1.9, debhelper (>= 5.0.7), dpatch, libncurses5-dev, libsieve2-dev (>= 2.1.12), libglib2.0-dev, libgmime-2.0-2-dev, libldap2-dev, libzdb-dev, libmhash-dev, libevent-dev, pkg-config, libtool, asciidoc, xmlto, po-debconf
Standards-Version: 3.7.3

Package: dbmail
Architecture: any
Pre-Depends: adduser
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, ucf (>= 0.30)
Provides: imap-server, pop3-server
Suggests: sqlite3
Description: base package for the dbmail email solution
 DBMAIL is a collection of programs that allows email to be
 stored in and retrieved from a sql database.
 .
 It supports MySQL, PostgreSQL and Sqlite3 as database backends, LDAP
 and Sieve.
 .
 Supported client protocols are: POP3, IMAP4, LMTP.
 .
